    - name: Get commit info
        id: commit
        env:
          COMMIT_MESSAGE: ${{ github.event.head_commit.message || inputs.image_tag || github.event_name }}
          EVENT_NAME: ${{ github.event_name }}
        run: |
          SHORT_SHA=$(echo "${{ github.sha }}" | cut -c1-7)
          MSG="${COMMIT_MESSAGE:-($EVENT_NAME)}"
          if [ -z "$MSG" ]; then
            MSG="($EVENT_NAME)"
          fi
          MSG=$(printf '%s' "$MSG" | tr '\r\n' ' ')
          {
            echo "short_sha=$SHORT_SHA"
            echo "message<<EOF"
            echo "$MSG"
            echo "EOF"
          } >> "$GITHUB_OUTPUT"
----------------------------------------


What this block does
✅ Gets the commit message
COMMIT_MESSAGE: ${{ github.event.head_commit.message }}
Reads the latest commit message.


Used in notification ::

✅ Gets the short commit ID
SHORT_SHA=$(echo "${{ github.sha }}" | cut -c1-7)

Example:

Full SHA : a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8
Short SHA: a1b2c3d
✅ Uses fallback value

If commit message is empty,

Commit Message
      ↓
Image Tag
      ↓
Event Name

It always picks whichever is available ::

✅ Removes new lines
tr '\r\n' ' '

Converts

Fixed login
Added validation

into

Fixed login Added validation ::

✅ Saves values as outputs
>> $GITHUB_OUTPUT

Makes the values available to later steps.

Example:

${{ steps.commit.outputs.short_sha }}

${{ steps.commit.outputs.message }}
One-line memory tip

Use this block in notification jobs to collect the commit message and short commit ID, then pass them to the Notify Teams/Slack step.

